The Kenya Rainwater Association has urged the government to pass laws that ensure all buildings incorporate rainwater harvesting.Florence Chepkoech, the communication officer, said this will ensure no water goes to waste. The government plans to launch the National Water Harvesting and Storage Authority next week.While marking the world water day in Taita Taveta last month, Water CS Simon Chelugui said the government will this month launch the NWHSA to streamline rainwater harvesting.This is in line with the Water Act, 2016. The ongoing rains have wreaked havoc and at least 20 people have died from flooding. Property has been destroyed and roads have been cut off. The Rainwater agency has urged Kenyans to harvest every drop of water this season.  Click here for the latest political news